## Editor UI

You will become familiar with the following concepts:
- The editor's windows
- Creating a GameObject
- Moving the Scene view
- Reseting the windows layout

![a](./UI%20Overview.png)
###### _My prefered editor layout_ 

> [!TIP]
> The editor seems intimidating at first,   
> but you can ignore most of the options to focus on the most important ones.  
> You will be used to it in 5 minutes anyways.

**Here are the windows I use most:** 
| Name | Usage |
| - | - |
| **Hierarchy** | List the game object present in your scene |
| **Inspector** | Shows the components of the selected game object |
| **Scene** | Edit the game objects that are present in the loaded scenes |
| **Game** | The scene as rendered by the in-game camera |
| **Project** | The file explorer of your project. Browse and drag-drop the game's assets from here |
| **Console** | Print from the components |

Here are some other options I use sometimes :
| Name | Usage | Access |
| - | - | - |
| **Lightning** | Edit/Bake the project's lightning | `Window`>`Rendering` |
| **Package Manager** | Import package of assets | `Window`>`Package Management` |
| **Build Profiles** | The project's building options | `File`>`Build Profiles` |

Do not worry much about them for now, but know that they will be back in the next task ;)   


### Tasks

![CubeLightPlane](./CubeLightPlane.png)

#### 1- Moving the view

[] Move the view with `Alt` + `Wheel Click`
[] Rotate the view around using `Alt` + `Left Click`
[] Unzoom with `Alt` + `Right Click`
[] Select an object using `Left click`
- Inside the hierarchy window
- Inside the Scene window   

[] Focus the view on the selected object by pressing `F` within the Scene window

#### 2- Adding GameObjects

[] Use `Right Click` in the Hierarchy to add
1. A plane _(Y position should be set to 0)_
2. A cube _(Y position should be set to 0.5)_
3. Any kind of light _(do not worry about making it work for now)_

[] Make the Light a child of the Cube _(see screenshot)_

#### 3- Using game objects edition modes

[] Select the `Main Camera`
[] Press `E` to enter `Rotate` mode
- Press the keys from `Q`_(or `A`)_ to `Y` to ente the different modes

[] Drag any of the 3 colored lines to edit the object 
[] Move and/or Rotate the Camera to make the Cube appear within the `Game` view

> [!TIP]
> You will update the `Transform` component to achieve this.    
> The component's parameters can be updated from Scene view or the Inspector window.
> You can click and drag on any of these parameters _(Rotation's `X` or `Y`)_ to change the value.

![CameraRotate](./CameraRotate.png)


#### 4- Customize your layout

Now, rearrange the window layout  

[] `Right Click`>`Close Tab` the windows' title to close it. Do it on all windows until only a single one is left.
[] Use the `Window` dropdown to restitute a layout that you like _(I recommand mine from the first screenshot if you are unsure)_

![Layout dropdown](./Layout.png)
###### The layout option will save you if you feel lost ;)

-----
You should now be confortable using Unity.  
**So let's get into game development now !**